  "texts": [
    "This concept of intelligent tracking with metasurfaces is paving the way for challenges in 6G wireless communication and the Internet of Things.While AI enhances metasurface systems, it also brings new opportunities for AI itself.",
    "As computer technology continues to advance, the capacity for electronic hardware to transmit and process information is approaching its limits.",
    "Optical devices, utilizing photons as carriers for information transfer, have demonstrated the ability for ultrafast parallel processing in complex and lengthy tasks, making them one of today's hottest research directions.",
    "ML algorithms, used to accelerate metasurface design, can also enable these trained metasurface systems to replace machine learning algorithms and form all-optical machine learning [241]- [243].",
    "Hougne et al. [244] proposed \"learning integrated sensing pipeline (LISP),\" which simultaneously optimizes the physical layer (reconfigurable metasurface) and the neural network processing layer for microwave sensing tasks, showed in Figure 14(d)."
  ],
